Refactor Plan: Full Optimization Program (Profitability + Loading Speed + SEO Completion)
Current State
Comply-Quick already has strong foundations: Stripe subscriptions/metered usage, PMF/churn capture, paywall/funnel events, broad feature modules, and existing SEO metadata/structured data.
Gaps are mostly in systematic optimization infrastructure: experimentation framework, expansion/dunning automation depth, CWV monitoring + budgets, strict third-party script governance, and final SEO hardening across all indexable routes.

Target State
A production-ready optimization system where:

Profitability loops (pricing/paywall experiments, churn recovery, expansion nudges) run continuously and are measurable.
Loading speed is protected by guardrails (CWV telemetry, budgets, CI enforcement, script loading policies).
SEO is fully hardened post-performance/profitability rollout (route-level metadata/schema consistency, crawl/index quality, internal linking completeness).
